# TypeScript Standards

## Types and Schemas

- All shared types derived from Zod schemas in `src/types/audit.ts`
- Use `z.infer<typeof Schema>` — never duplicate type definitions manually
- No `any` in `src/lib/scraper/`, `src/lib/metrics/`, or `src/lib/ai/`

## Error Handling

Use typed custom errors:

```ts
// ✅ Typed domain errors
export class FetchError extends Error {
  constructor(public readonly url: string, cause: unknown) {
    super(`Failed to fetch ${url}`);
    this.cause = cause;
  }
}

// ✅ Surface user-friendly messages in API responses
return NextResponse.json({ error: 'Could not reach that URL. Check it is publicly accessible.' }, { status: 422 });
```

## Null Safety

- `metaTitle` and `metaDescription` are `string | null` — handle both cases
- `altTextPercent` returns `0` when `imageCount === 0` (no division-by-zero)

## API Route Return Types

Always return a typed response shape — never `any` or untyped JSON:

```ts
// src/types/api.ts defines AuditResponse and AuditErrorResponse
return NextResponse.json<AuditResponse>(payload);
```
